1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:07,892
Here's the thing,  in a healthy cluster, partition leaders should be evenly distributed across brokers.

2
00:00:07,842 --> 00:00:15,157
If one broker holds most leaders, it handles disproportionate write and read load.

3
00:00:15,157 --> 00:00:25,736
auto.leader.rebalance.enable=true (default) triggers periodic rebalancing to restore even leader distribution.

4
00:00:25,736 --> 00:00:33,105
Monitor with kafka.server:type=ReplicaManager,name=LeaderCount.

